        "description": {
            "value": "<p>House Thrune has cast its tyrannical shadow over Cheliax for over 80 years, and you long to topple the dynasty and free southwest Avistan from its grip. You might be a spy for Andoran or another active combatant in the ongoing war, or perhaps you're a rebellious soul who grew up under Thrune's thumb and dreams of a better future. Whatever the case, you're a versed saboteur ready to destroy Cheliax's armies from behind enemy lines.</p>\n<p>Choose two attribute boosts. One must be to <strong>Dexterity</strong> or <strong>Charisma</strong>, and one is a free attribute boost.</p>\n<p>You're trained in either Deception or Thievery, as well as either the Cheliax Lore or Engineering Lore skill. If you chose Deception, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Lengthy Diversion] skill feat. If you chose Thievery, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Dirty Trick] skill feat.</p>"
